Parliament, Thursday 25 July 2019 – The National Council of Provinces, at its plenary sitting today, concluded policy debates on four budget votes.
	
	These were on Water and Sanitation (Vote 36), Human Settlements (Vote 38), Rural Development and Land Reform (Vote 39) and Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries (Vote 24).
	
	The National Council of Provinces is scheduled to consider and make decisions on the Appropriation Bill on 30 July. The National Assembly agreed to the Bill on Tuesday.
	
